-1.title: Whodunit
-1.plot: The employees of the Hollywood Z have a problem and they can't seem to find where it's coming from.

imdb.plot outline: It opens with Tori coloring her favorite, Superman. A kid comes up and asks her to color. After getting him to ask correctly, she gets up to get it for him, only for him to ask her to color Batman. Appalled, Tori explains why they don't let people color "whiny BatBabies" and she'll only let him color a real superhero. Overhearing this, Isabella and Carter realize how bad Tori's obsession has gotten. They try to confront her about it, only for her to explain that she is NOT obsessed. They try to get her to name someone she is attracted to besides Superman, for which Tori provides numerous examples - of actors who have portrayed Superman. When they get her to name someone with no relation to Superman, she gives a whole list, only to be interrupted when she smells something bad. CODE BROWN. Sent into a panic, the employees try to discover the cause of the smell, even going so far as to ban children from leaving and coming in. When they finally find it, they let kids come in, only to smell another smell. Just another day at the Hollywood Z.
imdb.title: The Z
plot: A mocumentary set at a well known gym/community center in the heart of Hollywood and its day-to-day dealings with ridiculous employees, sassy children, and uppity parents.::Danielle Silverstone
